<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Parkdale</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Across the river is the Bow River Pathway, which travels along the length of the Bow River and is a popular destination for jogging, hiking and biking/rollerblading. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The pathway is an excellent place to see the natural side of Calgary and breath in the fresh mountain air brought in by the water flow.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Two schools are located in Parkdale, a public elementary and a private academy.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Parkdale has easy access to medical, dental and chiropractic clinics located in the Kensington BRZ and facilities at Foothills Hospital and the Alberta Children’s Hospital. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Parkdale is also home to the Landmark Collaborative Health Centre, Carewest, and the Advanced Spinal Care Centre. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Adjacent to Alberta Children’s Hospital is the Ronald McDonald House Southern Alberta. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">In 2011, had a population of 2,317.</p>
        </div>
